<file path="docs/code-standards.md">
# Code Standards

## File Naming
- kebab-case for all files: `match-card.tsx`, `use-live-matches.ts`
- Max 200 lines per file - split if exceeded
- Descriptive names that self-document purpose for LLM tools

## TypeScript
- Strict mode enabled
- No `any` types - use proper interfaces/types
- Types in `src/types/` directory
- Zod for API response validation

## Components
- Functional components only (no class components)
- Props interface defined above component
- `React.memo` for list items and frequently re-rendered components
- Named exports preferred (easier refactoring)

## Hooks
- Custom hooks in `src/hooks/`
- TanStack Query hooks: prefix with `use-` (e.g., `use-live-matches.ts`)
- Zustand stores: suffix with `-store.ts`

## State Management
- **Server state** → TanStack Query (matches, scores, fixtures)
- **UI state** → Zustand (favorites, filters, settings)
- No useState for data that comes from API

## Styling
- NativeWind (Tailwind classes) for styling
- Dark mode first (sports apps typically dark)
- Color tokens in `tailwind.config.js`

## Error Handling
- TanStack Query for API error states
- ErrorBoundary at route level
- Graceful degradation with cached data when offline

## Testing
- Vitest for unit tests
- React Native Testing Library for component tests
- Test files: `*.test.ts` or `*.test.tsx`

## API Calls
- All API calls through `src/services/api-football-client.ts`
- Rate limit wrapper: max 100 req/day with smart caching
- Never call API directly from components

## Git
- Conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`
- No secrets/API keys committed
- Branch per feature
