<file path="docs/system-architecture.md">
# System Architecture

## Overview
Quick Score - React Native football live score app (Expo managed workflow).

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology | Version |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| Framework | Expo (managed) | 52.0+ |
| Runtime | React Native | 0.76+ |
| Navigation | Expo Router | v3 (file-based) |
| State (UI) | Zustand | 4.x |
| State (Server) | TanStack Query | 5.x |
| Real-time | react-use-websocket | 4.x |
| UI Components | Gluestack UI | v3 |
| Styling | NativeWind | latest |
| API | API-Football | Free tier |
| Storage | AsyncStorage | 1.22+ |
| Notifications | expo-notifications | 0.28+ |
| Build | EAS Build | - |

## App Structure

```
app/
├── (tabs)/
│   ├── _layout.tsx          # Bottom tab bar
│   ├── index.tsx            # Live Scores (home)
│   ├── fixtures.tsx         # Fixtures/Schedule
│   ├── standings.tsx        # League Tables
│   └── favorites.tsx        # Saved teams/matches
├── match/
│   └── [id].tsx             # Match Detail (dynamic)
├── settings.tsx             # Notifications & prefs
└── _layout.tsx              # Root layout (providers)
src/
├── components/
│   ├── match-card.tsx
│   ├── score-board.tsx
│   ├── fixture-item.tsx
│   ├── standings-table.tsx
│   └── live-indicator.tsx
├── hooks/
│   ├── use-live-matches.ts
│   ├── use-match-detail.ts
│   ├── use-standings.ts
│   └── use-fixtures.ts
├── stores/
│   ├── favorites-store.ts
│   ├── filters-store.ts
│   └── settings-store.ts
├── services/
│   ├── api-football-client.ts
│   ├── websocket-service.ts
│   └── notification-service.ts
└── types/
    ├── match.ts
    ├── player.ts
    └── league.ts
```

## Data Flow

```
API-Football HTTP ──┐
                    ├──► TanStack Query Cache ──► UI Components
WebSocket (live) ───┘

Zustand Store (favorites/filters) ──► UI Components

AsyncStorage ──► Offline fallback for TanStack Query
```

## Real-Time Strategy
- Live matches: WebSocket push every 2-5s (events only)
- Standings: HTTP poll every 30s (staleTime: 30000)
- Fixtures: HTTP poll every 5min (staleTime: 300000)
- Fallback: polling if WebSocket unavailable (API-Football free tier limitation)

## Key Screens
1. **Scores** - Live match feed with date/competition filters
2. **Fixtures** - Upcoming schedule (7-day view)
3. **Standings** - League tables (live updates)
4. **Favorites** - Saved teams & bookmarked matches
5. **Match Detail** - Lineups, events, stats, commentary
6. **Settings** - Notification preferences, theme

## Performance Targets
- Score update latency: <3s from event
- API response: <200ms
- Push notification delivery: 95% within 30s
</file>

